====Usage notes====
Often abbreviated to much simpler {{m|ja|才}}, for example in {{m|ja|何才||how old?}}, or {{m|ja||１才|1 year old}}, as opposed to {{m|ja|何歳||how old?}}, {{m|ja||１歳|1 year old}}. The phrase "twenty years old" ({{l|ja|二十歳}}) uses ''jukujikun'' reading and pronounced {{l|ja|はたち|tr=hatachi}} using the tradition Japanese counter ''tsu''/''chi''. Similar native-Japanese readings for “thirty years old” and beyond also occur more rarely.

